{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "easyvtc-rgpd-sprint7",
    "name": "EasyVTC API — RGPD (Sprint 7)",
    "description": "# EasyVTC — Module RGPD\n\n## Conformité\n- **France** : RGPD (Règlement général sur la protection des données)\n- **Sénégal** : Loi 2008-12 sur la protection des données personnelles (CDP)\n\n## Endpoints couverts\n- `GET    /users/:id/data-export`   → Export JSON de toutes les données personnelles (droit d'accès Art.15)\n- `DELETE /users/:id/anonymize`    → Anonymisation / suppression RGPD (droit à l'effacement Art.17)\n\n## Logique métier\n\n### Export\n- Retourne toutes les données personnelles : profil, réservations, notifications, évaluations, favoris, documents\n- Accessible par l'utilisateur lui-même ou par un admin\n\n### Anonymisation\n- Efface l'identité (email → `anonyme_XXX@deleted.local`, nom → `Anonyme`)\n- Conserve les données comptables (factures, bons de commande) pour conformité fiscale\n- Invalide la session Supabase Auth\n- Irréversible — tester avec un compte dédié\n\n⚠️ **ATTENTION** : Le test d'anonymisation est destructif. Utiliser un compte de test dédié.\n\n## Variables sauvegardées\n- `admin_token`, `client_token`, `driver_token`\n- `client_user_id`",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url",       "value": "http://localhost:4000", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "admin_token",    "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "client_token",   "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "driver_token",   "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "client_user_id", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [

    {
      "name": "🔐 Setup — Tokens",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login Admin",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth","login"] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"admin@test.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Admin1234!\"\n}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
            "pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
            "pm.collectionVariables.set('admin_token', data.access_token);"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "Login Client — récupère client_user_id",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth","login"] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"client@test.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Client1234!\"\n}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
            "pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
            "pm.collectionVariables.set('client_token', data.access_token);",
            "pm.collectionVariables.set('client_user_id', data.user.id);",
            "console.log('client_user_id:', data.user.id);"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "Login Driver",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth","login"] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"driver@test.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Driver1234!\"\n}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
            "pm.collectionVariables.set('driver_token', data.access_token);"
          ]}}]
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "📤 Export des données (droit d'accès — Art.15 RGPD)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /users/:id/data-export — le client exporte ses propres données",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/users/{{client_user_id}}/data-export",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["users","{{client_user_id}}","data-export"]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Export contient les sections requises', () => {",
            "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
            "  pm.expect(data).to.have.property('profile');",
            "  pm.expect(data).to.have.property('reservations');",
            "  pm.expect(data).to.have.property('notifications');",
            "  console.log('Sections:', Object.keys(data).join(', '));",
            "  console.log('Réservations exportées:', data.reservations?.length ?? 0);",
            "});",
            "pm.test('Profil contient les champs personnels', () => {",
            "  const { data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(data.profile).to.have.property('email');",
            "  pm.expect(data.profile).to.have.property('first_name');",
            "  pm.expect(data.profile).to.have.property('last_name');",
            "  pm.expect(data.profile).to.have.property('created_at');",
            "  pm.expect(data.profile.id).to.equal(pm.collectionVariables.get('client_user_id'));",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /users/:id/data-export — admin exporte les données d'un client",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/users/{{client_user_id}}/data-export",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["users","{{client_user_id}}","data-export"]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200 — admin peut exporter les données de tout utilisateur', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('ok = true', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().ok).to.be.true);",
            "console.log('Export admin OK — sections:', Object.keys(pm.response.json().data).join(', '));"
          ]}}]
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "🗑️ Anonymisation (droit à l'effacement — Art.17 RGPD)",
      "description": "⚠️ DESTRUCTIF — Utiliser uniquement avec un compte de test dédié.\nL'anonymisation est irréversible : l'email et le nom sont écrasés, la session est invalidée.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "⚠️ DELETE /users/:id/anonymize — LECTURE SEULE (ne pas exécuter sans compte de test)",
          "description": "Cette requête anonymise définitivement le compte.\nElle efface l'identité mais conserve les données comptables.\n\n⚠️ Remplacer {{client_user_id}} par l'ID d'un compte de test DÉDIÉ avant d'exécuter.",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{client_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/users/{{client_user_id}}/anonymize",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["users","{{client_user_id}}","anonymize"]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200 — anonymisation réussie', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Confirmation d\\'anonymisation', () => {",
            "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
            "  pm.expect(data).to.have.property('anonymized_at');",
            "  console.log('Compte anonymisé le:', data.anonymized_at);",
            "  console.log('Champs effacés:', data.fields_anonymized);",
            "});",
            "// Après anonymisation, le token est invalide",
            "pm.collectionVariables.set('client_token', '');"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "⚠️ DELETE /users/:id/anonymize — par l'admin (LECTURE SEULE)",
          "description": "Un admin peut déclencher l'anonymisation d'un compte sur demande RGPD.\n⚠️ Utiliser un compte de test dédié.",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/users/{{client_user_id}}/anonymize",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["users","{{client_user_id}}","anonymize"]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200 — admin peut anonymiser', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('ok = true', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().ok).to.be.true);"
          ]}}]
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "🔒 Contrôle d'accès",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "[401] GET /users/:id/data-export sans token",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/users/{{client_user_id}}/data-export",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["users","{{client_user_id}}","data-export"]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 401', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "[403] Driver — accès aux données d'un autre utilisateur",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{driver_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/users/{{client_user_id}}/data-export",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["users","{{client_user_id}}","data-export"]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 403 — accès refusé (pas le propriétaire ni admin)', () => pm.response.to.have.status(403));"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "[400] GET — user_id pas un UUID",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/users/not-a-uuid/data-export",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["users","not-a-uuid","data-export"]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 400 ou 404', () => {",
            "  pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.oneOf([400, 404]);",
            "});",
            "pm.test('ok = false', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().ok).to.be.false);"
          ]}}]
        }
      ]
    }

  ]
}
